<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-WarBegan-0">^ <a href="#cite_ref-WarBegan_0-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WarBegan_0-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Diem instituted a policy of death penalty against any communist activity in 1956. The Vietcong began an assassination campaign in early 1957. An article by French scholar <a href="/wiki/Bernard_Fall" title="Bernard Fall" class="mw-redirect">Bernard Fall</a> published in July 1958 concluded that a new war had begun. The first large unit military action was on September 26, 1959, when the Vietcong ambushed two ARVN companies.<a href="http://www.mtholyoke.edu/acad/intrel/pentagon/pent14.htm" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.mtholyoke.edu/acad/intrel/pentagon/pent14.htm" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
